                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/668: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-10T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 10, 1929—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 11—9:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1120. Following from American Consul at Harbin: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“December 9, 5 p.m. Chinese officials connected with the railway
                            dejected. It would appear that the Chinese authorities in general are
                            willing to grant any Soviet demands in order to restore normal
                            conditions in North Manchuria. It is reported that a Soviet armored
                            train has come as far east as station Charomte [<hi rend="italic"
                                >Chalamute</hi>] and the [<hi rend="italic">that?</hi>] Red Mongol
                            cavalry detachments are moving about near Hailar Station. There is some
                            uneasiness in regard to how successful the authorities will be in
                            sending south superfluous troops including enormous number out of hand,
                            many of whom will become brigands, and in regard to taking care of the
                            thousands of penniless Russian and Chinese refugees who are moving down
                            the railway line and into Harbin.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
